{"key":"post-8720896","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>8720896</id>\n<content>4 air exchanges per hour is recommended, but if done with a pump, it's likely to dry out your terrarium.&amp;nbsp; If your tray is too big for the terrarium, then use a smaller tray or larger terrarium.&amp;nbsp; If you want to exchange air properly, it isn't with an aquarium pump.&amp;nbsp; Exchange the air totally in 20 seconds by fanning vigorously or running a large fan, and then let it sit until the next fanning session.&amp;nbsp; This allows the humidity to recover.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Large trays perform better in mini-greenhouses.&amp;nbsp; Terrariums are better suited to small trays or cakes.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>8721195</next>\n<prev>8720665</prev>\n<first>8706961</first>\n<last>8782026</last>\n<when>1217810577</when>\n<utime>08/04/08 03:42 AM</utime>\n</post>"}